d pain can procure him some great pleasure. To take a trivial example, which of us ever undertakes laborious physical exercise, except to obtain some advantage from it? But who has any right to find fault with a man who chooses to enjoy a pleasure that has no annoying consequences, or one who avoids a pain that produces no resultant pleasure?\"\n<h3>Section 1.10.33 of \"de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum\", written by Cicero in 45 BC</h3>\n\"At vero eos et accusamus et iusto odio dignissimos ducimus qui blanditiis praesentium voluptatum deleniti atque corrupti quos dolores et quas molestias excepturi sint occaecati cupiditate non provident, similique sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollitia animi, id est laborum et dolorum fuga. Et harum quidem rerum facilis est et expedita distinctio. Nam libero tempore, cum soluta nobis est eligendi optio cumque nihil impedit quo minus id quod maxime placeat facere possimus, omnis voluptas assumenda est, omnis dolor repellendus. Temporibus autem quibusdam et aut officiis debitis aut rerum necessitatibus saepe eveniet ut et voluptates repudiandae sint et molestiae non recusandae. Itaque earum rerum hic tenetur a sapiente delectus, ut aut reiciendis voluptatibus maiores alias consequatur aut perferendis doloribus asperiores repellat.\"\n<!--nextpage-->\n<h3>1914 translation by H. Rackham</h3>\n\"On the other hand, we denounce with righteous indignation and dislike men who are so beguiled and demoralized by the charms of pleasure of the moment, so blinded by desire, that they cannot foresee the pain and trouble that are bound to ensue; and equal blame belongs to those who fail in their duty through weakness of will, which is the same as saying through shrinking from toil and pain. These cases are perfectly simple and easy to distinguish. In a free hour, when our power of choice is untrammelled and when nothing prevents our being able to do what we like best, every pleasure is to be welcomed and every pain avoided. But in certain circumstances and owing to the claims of duty or the obligations of business it will frequently occur that pleasures have to be repudiated and annoyances accepted. The wise man therefore always holds in these matters to this principle of selection: he rejects pleasures to secure other greater pleasures, or else he endures pains to avoid worse pains.\"','Introduction to Social Media','','draft','closed','closed','','introduction-to-social-media','','','2016-02-01 10:00:13','2016-02-01 15:00:13','',0,'http://vibethemes.com/envato/wplms/?post_type=unit&#038;p=213',0,'unit','',0),(215,1,'2014-01-31 15:33:16','2014-01-31 15:33:16','<h3>Social Media</h3>\nBear claw tootsie roll I love powder donut cheesecake. Pie lemon drops dragÃ©e powder chocolate dessert pudding. I love sugar plum cupcake tart apple pie pudding sweet roll cheesecake. Apple pie brownie powder lemon drops dragÃ©e macaroon applicake croissant. I love lemon drops icing candy canes chocolate cake cotton candy pie marzipan. Chocolate bar bear claw cupcake chocolate cake unerdwear.com I love gingerbread topping. Chupa chups pie dessert cotton candy macaroon. Icing jelly tart oat cake chocolate I love brownie jelly.\n\n[video width=\"640\" height=\"360\" mp4=\"http://vibethemes.com/envato/wplms/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/big_buck_bunny.mp4\"][/video]\n\nSweet roll powder muffin I love chocolate brownie candy canes macaroon soufflÃ©. Chocolate cake icing tart brownie I love. Muffin candy jelly beans gummi bears. I love tootsie roll candy tootsie roll jelly beans I love bear claw. Candy gingerbread sugar plum gummi bears. I love I love chocolate jelly beans gummi bears carrot cake dessert. I love cotton candy carrot cake.\n\nChocolate cake tart fruitcake candy apple pie. SoufflÃ© I love marshmallow tiramisu chocolate bar cookie chupa chups. Donut marshmallow marzipan halvah toffee cheesecake ice cream toffee I love. Halvah danish I love powder tart. Cupcake I love fruitcake fruitcake lemon drops tiramisu halvah muffin